cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI 

The paper deals with deep learning object detection algorithm for medical image analysis, specifically for breast cancer detection in mammography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel top likelihood loss and a new sampling procedure, which are related to machine learning techniques, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that cs.MM (Medical Imaging) is another possible sub-category. The paper also involves similarity loss and classification of patients, which are related to information retrieval and artificial intelligence, respectively, indicating that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories.
